						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab near the tuṁbu in S. No. 1.</hi></p>						

						<p>This record of about the <hi rend="bold">9th century A.D.</hi> states that when <hi rend="bold">Kattiyara</hi> “was ruling the earth”, <hi rend="bold">Dōsi,</hi> who was governing <hi rend="bold">Banavāsi Twelve-thousand</hi> remitted on the occasion of an eclipse, a portion of the tax of <hi rend="bold">Saṅgamūr,</hi> after washing the feet of the <hi rend="italic">mahājanas</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Mugunda.</hi></p>						

						<p>Published on p. 253 of <hi rend="italic">Ep. Ind.,</hi> Vol. VI.</p>						

						</summary>
